Motorists can brace themselves for yet another fuel price hike this month, effective from midnight on Tuesday The price of 93 octane petrol – both unleaded (ULP) and lead replacement (LRP) – will go up by 26c/l and 95 octane (ULP & LRP) by 23c/l, the Department of Energy said in a statement on Sunday. Diesel 0,05% sulphur would rise by 26c/l and diesel 0,005% sulphur by 24c/l. The wholesale price of illuminating paraffin would increase by 22c/l and the single maximum national retail price by 30c/l. The maximum retail price for LP Gas would increase by 37c/kg. READ MORE: How to survive June’s massive petrol price hike The average international product prices of petrol and diesel and illuminating paraffin decreased during the period under review (1-28 June), but the rand depreciated against the dollar on average, the department said. – African News Agency